title: Queen - Live at the Rainbow
description:
In 1974 Queen decide to film two of their concerts in the famous Rainbow Theatre in London (19th and 20th November). The film is then shown in British cinemas and in 1992 remastered and released on VHS in a box set called Box Of Tricks. It perfectly captures the atmosphere of the early Queen gigs - unfortunately, the recording is heavily edited. The video itself apparently comes from 20th November but it&#039;s possible some parts are from the previous night.

    * Procession
    * Now I&#039;m Here
    * Ogre Battle
    * White Queen (As It Began)
    * In The Lap Of The Gods
    * Killer Queen
    * The March Of The Black Queen
    * Bring Back That Leroy Brown
    * Son And Daughter
    * Guitar solo
    * Father To Son (cut)
    * Keep Yourself Alive (cut)
    * Liar (cut)
    * Son & Daughter reprise
    * Stone Cold Crazy
    * In The Lap of the Gods... revisited
    * Jailhouse Rock (cut)
    * God Save The Queen

NOTE: This is not my Rip and I can not remember where I even got it I have had it so long, but its clean and is a good quality MPEG so please enjoy :)
